
Function: MKFUNARG

Syntax:   (MKFUNARG arg1 arg2)

 arg1 (required, evaluated) - a LISP object that can be APPLY'ed.
 arg2 (required, evaluated) - an evaluation environment.

Returns:

 An interpreted lexical closure (funarg) whose function component
 is arg1 and whose environment component is arg2.

Processing:

Errors signaled:

 None (so watch out!).

Notes:

 MKFUNARG is used by the evaluator to process the FUNCTION special form.
 Nobody else should be using this function.

